schemas.description: The Southern Photometric Local Universe Survey (S-PLUS) -- Data Release 4

tables.description: Psf yields photometry done using dophot on each image, for a given filter, using only that image as a detection image.
Dual yields photometry done using Sextractor on each image, for a given filter, using as a detection image the sum of g+r+i+z.
Single yields photometry done using Sextractor on each image, for a given filter, using only that image as a detection image.
Bit-flag produced during the visual inspection of the calibrated catalogs.

Single-point estimates (SPEs) of the photometric redshifts and probability distribution functions (PDFs) based on galaxy spectroscopy for all objects. Obtained using a Bayesian Mixture Density Network model.
Photometric redshifts focusing on quasars. Contains the SPEs for all methods and the PDFs for the Bayesian Mixture Density Networks (bmdn) and FlexCoDE (flex).

Provides a unique identifier across different data releases for each astronomical object in the S-PLUS catalog. It is designed to eliminate duplicate detections, ensuring that observations of the same object from different fields or exposures are consolidated under a single unique identifier.
Photometric classification of stars, galaxies, and quasars for all sources including the estimated probabilities for each class.
